did.unittitle:
ALS to Mrs. D.S. Jordan; an instrument to do the will of her loved ones;
                  solicitude for the students; witnesses the Passion Play; why she likes
                  Kissingen

LS to Dr. Jordan. Good work of students in extinguishing fire;
                    concerning Lubin prize; would like students to consider Land Loan Bill; homesick
                    in New York.

AL. Wants to forget anxieties; is taking the cure at Bad Kissingen;
                    wonders at happiness of peasants; glad that affair with Dr. Brown is arranged
                    [signature cut out]

LS. Missionaries in China useless; at Kissingen, going to Oberammergau;
                    regarding a conservatory of music at Stanford; anxious about Mr.
                    Nash

LS. welcome news of football victory; visited Harvard and Yale;
                    anecdote re ancestor John Lathrop; visit with Lathrop relatives in Norwich,
                    CT

Jordan to Lathrop, Cooper just wants to keep expenses within his income;
                  advises not to give more than the board bill, with room rent and registration fees
                  being waived

ALS re arrangements for unveiling of Fr. Junipero statue in Monterey;
                  includes letter to Casanova from Society of California Pioneers of May 21,
                  1891

scopecontent.p:
Letters among Clinton Day (architect), Jane Stanford, George Crothers, Charles
              Lathrop, and Charles Hodges; estimates and receipts; agreements with Clinton Day;
              power of attorney to three trustees for matters relating to library construction
